BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:sap-s4hana-watch-2026-w28-release-planning@codex.local
DTSTAMP:20260629T080959Z
SUMMARY:SAP S/4HANA Cloud watch: 2608 APJ release planning
DTSTART:20260708T030000Z
DTEND:20260708T040000Z
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
LOCATION:SAP Preferred Success / SAP Learning Hub
DESCRIPTION:SAP Preferred Success APJ release planning session for SAP Cloud ERP 2608. SAP lists the APJ English session for July 8, 13:00-14:00 AEST. SAP says the session covers 2608 release dates, the upgrade process, the new system maintenance schedule starting from September, RASD impact analysis, and release call-to-action items.\n\nTimezone shown to user: Australia/Sydney.\nCalendar status: Free.\nSource: SAP Preferred Success: Join Our SAP Cloud ERP 2608 Release Planning Session.\nCodex SAP maintenance watch id: 2026-W28-RELEASE-PLANNING
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT12H
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:SAP 2608 release planning session reminder
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:sap-s4hana-watch-2026-w29@codex.local
DTSTAMP:20260629T080959Z
SUMMARY:SAP S/4HANA Cloud watch: 2608 Test upgrade
DTSTART:20260718T120000Z
DTEND:20260718T160000Z
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
LOCATION:SAP S/4HANA Cloud Public Edition online schedule
DESCRIPTION:2608 major upgrade for Test systems. SAP's 2608 upgrade guidance indicates T-Tenant upgrades to 2608 with HFC02 on 18-19 July 2026. Preliminary 2608 What's New and Product Assistance content is available for upgrade preparation through the What's New Viewer and RASD. SAP's 2608 Early Release Series runs 13-17 July 2026 and includes Extensibility, Finance, SAP Activate, Cloud ALM, and Test Automation Tool topics; the static source page does not expose a reliable session timezone, so exact session entries were not created. Customer action now tracked: SAP IAM guidance says successor IAM apps are inactive by default from 2602; before 2608, check predecessor app usage, activate successor IAM apps in business roles, validate with key users, and transport changes to Test and Production. Priority IAM successor IDs include F3516A_TRAN, F3425A_TRAN, F1443B_TRAN, F3883A_TRAN, F3915A_TRAN, F7280A_TRAN, F0956B_TRAN, and F9104_TRAN. Product update tracked: 2608 adds multi-processor workflow approval controls for two- and three-person approvals plus validation callbacks. RASD 2026 update tracked: use What's New change history, Last Modified On filtering, and RASD impact-card navigation for changed extensibility objects, where-used lists, impacted catalogs, IAM apps, and renamed app tiles. Newly tracked product updates: SAP BTP ABAP Environment 2608 pre-upgrade testing can be nominated for 17 July 08:00-16:00 CET, which is 17 July 17:00 to 18 July 01:00 AEST if SAP's CET label is interpreted literally; Explore Migration Objects adds 2602.4/2608 availability, scope-item status, and dependency-graph features for migration planning; SAP Asset Management describes AI-assisted maintenance notifications and planning; SAP Sales Billing adds Advanced Down Payment Processing with milestone billing; Project Billing excludes project-related postings to revenue and sales-deduction G/L accounts from billing processes under the 2608 account-type check; SAP Treasury Business Partner workflow controls add four-eyes governance and approval traceability for sensitive counterparty and payment-relevant data changes; EBRR dynamic fiscal-period determination adds Current Fiscal Period and Previous Fiscal Period options for recurring revenue-recognition close jobs across sales orders, projects, service documents, provider contracts, and revenue contracts. Decentralized EWM/QM integration for SAP Cloud ERP two-tier scenarios now tracks warehouse-side quality inspection with QIE and stock synchronization back to SAP Cloud ERP. Clean-core wrapper guidance now tracks wrapper interfaces around classic APIs and internal objects for ABAP Cloud-friendly extensibility. Outbound-delivery stock-warning custom logic now tracks BAdI LE_SHP_DELIVERY_FINAL_CHECK, stock checks before delivery save, and separate API message behavior. API-created delivery stock-shortage handling now tracks BAdI LE_SHP_SAVE_DOCUMENT_PREPARE, custom field YY1_Message, and SAP's note that API-created delivery warnings can be ignored unless handled as errors or persisted messages. EPPM financial-planning custom value types now track CAPEX/OPEX-style cost splits through integration customizing and BAdI RPM_FICO_INT. Origin Profit Centers now track project-margin reporting by responsible and contributing profit centers through a Universal Journal attribute. CBC 5-country rollout planning now tracks the SAP Central Business Configuration delta rule for country additions and main-line / parallel-line merge or rebase planning. Additional ERP feed product signals now tracked: sales-order developer extensibility via BAdI SD_SLS_END_OF_FINALIZE for issue-summary custom fields, now modified 29 June 2026 with details for custom field YY1_ISSUE_SUMMARY_SDH, enhancement spot ES_SD_SLS_DEV_EXTEND, method IF_SD_SLS_END_OF_FINALIZE~MODIFY_FIELDS, simulation-mode skip logic, and the generated control flag required for writes; EBRR company-code and ledger range scheduling; external revenue recognition key derivation for project-based sales in CFD 2602.3; Joule/two-tier planning signals for cross-tier constraints and cross-ATP checks; and SAP Business AI assistant/agent/skill concept signals for SAP Cloud ERP. SAP updated the Business AI article again on 1 July 2026 AEST; no maintenance-window or customer-action date change was detected. Full HFC02 attachment details are still pending until SAP publishes the 2608 patch collection note.\n\nTimezone shown to user: Australia/Sydney.\nCalendar status: Free.\nSource: SAP S/4HANA Cloud Public Edition, 3-System Landscape - Upgrade & Maintenance Schedule plus SAP 2608 upgrade guidance, preliminary 2608 What's New guidance, RASD 2026 update, Early Release Series page, IAM app activation guidance, 2608 workflow approvals product update, BTP ABAP Environment 2608 pre-upgrade guidance, Explore Migration Objects 2602.4/2608 update, Asset Management autonomous agents update, Advanced Down Payment milestone billing update, Project Billing account-type check guidance, Treasury Business Partner workflow-control guidance, EBRR dynamic fiscal-period guidance, decentralized EWM/QM integration update, clean-core wrapper guidance, outbound-delivery custom-logic guidance, API delivery stock-shortage guidance, EPPM custom-value-type guidance, Origin Profit Center guidance, CBC 5-country rollout guidance, SAP Community ERP product update RSS feed, and SAP Business AI Assistant/Agent product update, modified again 1 July 2026 AEST without a detected schedule or customer-action date change.\nCodex SAP maintenance watch id: 2026-W29
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT12H
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:SAP S/4HANA Cloud watch window reminder
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:sap-s4hana-watch-2026-w31@codex.local
DTSTAMP:20260629T080959Z
SUMMARY:SAP S/4HANA Cloud watch: 2608 Starter / other upgrade
DTSTART:20260801T120000Z
DTEND:20260802T120000Z
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
LOCATION:SAP S/4HANA Cloud Public Edition online schedule
DESCRIPTION:2608 major upgrade for Starter and other systems. SAP's 2608 upgrade guidance indicates other tenants upgrade with HFC03 on 1-2 August 2026, and T-Tenant receives HFC03 for new feature preview. Preliminary 2608 What's New and Product Assistance content is available for upgrade preparation through the What's New Viewer and RASD. Customer action remains active: complete the IAM successor app activation review before this upgrade weekend if affected predecessor apps are used. RASD follow-up: use change-history deltas, Last Modified On filtering, and impact-card navigation to review scope-specific changes. Full HFC03 attachment details are still pending until SAP publishes the 2608 patch collection note.\n\nTimezone shown to user: Australia/Sydney.\nCalendar status: Free.\nSource: SAP S/4HANA Cloud Public Edition, 3-System Landscape - Upgrade & Maintenance Schedule plus SAP 2608 upgrade guidance, preliminary 2608 What's New guidance, RASD 2026 update, and IAM app activation guidance.\nCodex SAP maintenance watch id: 2026-W31
